**** Rhetoric
- "Rhetoric is the ability in each particular case to discover the
  available means of persuasion."
- "Rhetoric is a mode of altering reality, not by the direct
  application of energy to objects, but by the creation of discourse
  which changes reality through the mediation of thought and action."
- "The use of words by human agents to form attitudes or induce
  actions in other human agents."
- "The use of language as a symbolic means of inducing cooperation in
  beings that by nature respond to symbols."
